org.devgateway.toolkit.persistence.validator

Class FMConstraintsConfigurer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.devgateway.toolkit.persistence.validator.FMConstraintsConfigurer

  • @Component
public class FMConstraintsConfigurer
extends java.lang.Object
    Programmatically add constraints to HibernateValidator. Takes all constraints provided by ConstraintInfoProvider and adds them programmatically to the validator.

      • getGroupForClass

        private java.lang.Class<?> getGroupForClass(java.lang.Class<?> javaType)
        Generates a bean validation group for a specific class. Group is an interface that extends from NonDraft and is generated in the same package as the requested class. Name will be appended Checks. Example: for Tender will generate TenderChecks group.

      • makeGroupForClass

      • getGroupSequenceProviderForClass

      • makeGroupSequenceProviderForClass

        private java.lang.Class makeGroupSequenceProviderForClass(java.lang.Class<?> javaType)
        Generates a class that can be used in @GroupSequenceProvider for a specific entity. The class extends from AbstractFMGroupSequenceProvider and the generated constructor will invoke super with the appropriate parameters.

        For Tender will generate the following class:

             public class TenderGroupServiceProvider extends AbstractFMGroupSequenceProvider {
         public TenderGroupServiceProvider() {
             super(TenderChecks.class, Tender.class);
         }
     }
